<br>
<br>
1) Mesmerization: This spell quite obviously rocks (didn't it use to have a 4 mob cap?), the one problem is the self mez part, especially when things are in tight.  I seem to be mezzing myself more and more with it, on the other hand nothing shuts down a train or tough spot like mesmerization!  Just wondering if there's a way to curtail the self mezzes or if it is normal for the enchanter to spend part of his day self medicated <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Often there's one other resist and the angry mob will gratefully come over and wake me up so i can enthrall it and be free.<br>
<br>
2) Targetting: This drives me nuts, it's my number one beef in EQ.  Am I missing something here?  I'd love to enthrall each mob separately, but sometimes i just can't target them.  Is there a key or macro i'm missing?  Assist is great for attacking group enemy number one, but of course I need to target every mob except for the one we're beating on.  This just leads me to dump more mesmerizations on the stack of mobs...which often does the job, but which just seems sloppy to me.  Even in situations where we aren't fighting a 16 armed lizard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and they're nicely spaced out i often have trouble targetting any given mob.  Verant fix this dammit!<br>
<br>
oh and just for fun 3) Alacrity, or Augmentation? - Discuss hehe.  Tanks seem to prefer Alacrity :J)  How much mana do you usually use on buffing?  I just through them out when i can afford it, but in a place like CT where everything can go to hell awful fast i tend to be a mana whore and stick almost to exclusively to mezzing (and tashani where possibly).<br>
<br>
